title: 3 still unaccounted for in collapsed Iowa building as documents reveal over 100 city interactions
description: Three people are still unaccounted for in the 116-year-old Iowa building that collapsed Sunday, police said Thursday.

title: Ex-teacher at Ye's Donda Academy says she was fired after parents complained her class had no books
description: A third former teacher from Ye’s private Christian school is suing the Donda Academy and the rapper formerly known as Kanye West, alleging that the building was unsafe and that she was dismissed after parents complained her classroom had no books.

title: National Eating Disorders Association pulls chatbot after users say it gave harmful dieting tips
description: NEDA said it has disabled its wellness chatbot after two users reported the program gave dieting advice that promoted disordered eating behaviors.

title: Senate racing to vote on the debt ceiling deal as soon as Thursday night
description: The Senate is working to pass the debt ceiling deal negotiated by President Joe Biden and Speaker Kevin McCarthy by the end of the week.

title: Train carrying hazardous materials derails and closes highway in Minnesota
description: A train containing some hazardous materials derailed Wednesday in northwest Minnesota near the Canada border, forcing the closure of a highway, officials said.

title: Special counsel has obtained a tape of Trump discussing a classified document he kept after leaving office
description: Special Counsel Jack Smith's office has obtained a recording of Donald Trump discussing a classified document that he had taken from his time at the White House.

title: Trump attorneys seek recusal of judge in New York criminal case
description: Attorneys for Donald Trump have filed a motion seeking to have a judge recuse himself from the Manhattan criminal case against the former president.

title: Amazon to pay $30 million for privacy violations
description: Amazon will pay more than $30 million to settle allegations that it violated customers’ privacy. Nearly $6 million stems from its Ring camera division giving employees and third-party contractors unrestricted access to customers' sensitive video, and the other $25 million comes after failing to delete certain recordings from its Alexa voice assistant.

title: Russian mercenaries exploit a war-torn African nation as they lead Putin’s fight in Ukraine
description: Central African Republic President Faustin-Archange Touadéra called in the Russians in 2017. Since then, Wagner mercenaries have extended their control.

title: 'What happened to Ray?': Family of Native American man killed by Border Patrol in Arizona wants to know why he was shot
description: A relative of a man killed by Border Patrol in Arizona said she was talking to him before he was shot and he said he had asked Border Patrol for help.

title: Instead of door-knocking, they were at the casino: Inside the flawed GOP turnout operation
description: A few weeks before last fall’s midterm elections, a paid canvasser in Nevada did what thousands of door-knockers across the country were doing: They went on an app and marked off the homes they had visited that day.

title: What is berberine, the supplement dubbed 'nature's Ozempic' on social media?
description: Berberine is getting attention on social media for claims it can help people lose weight naturally. Learn more about the supplement, including its risks and side effects.

title: As the U.S. government expands UFO investigations, a new group forms for pilots who spot them
description: The first active duty military pilot to come forward to Congress about UFOs is starting a first-of-its-kind non-profit.

title: A break-glass option, gumbo and a bike ride: How the debt ceiling deal got done
description: Thee House passed the deal Wednesday, capping a 36-day scramble at the White House and on Capitol Hill to avert economic catastrophe ahead of the default deadline.

title: McCarthy speaks after House passes debt ceiling bill
description: House Speaker Kevin McCarthy spoke moments after the House passed the debt ceiling bill in a late-night vote just days ahead of the deadline to avoid a catastrophic U.S. default.
